daily_routine: Each dawn, she would sit by the muddy Yangtze waters with her bamboo
  flute, playing the old river songs her grandmother taught her - melodies that once
  guided fishermen and celebrated the 'Goddess of the Yangtze'. Now cargo ships pass
  every few minutes, their engines so loud she can't hear her own music
